reasoning='The task is to create a Spectre netlist for a 5T OTA that meets certain performance specifications. I need to ensure the netlist follows the given format exactly, uses the correct transistor models (tsmc18dN for NMOS and tsmc18dP for PMOS), and includes the necessary ports (vin, vip, vout, VSS, VDD and ibp10u). The performance specifications involve DC gain, unity-gain frequency, common-mode rejection ratio, and input common-mode range, which guide the sizing of the transistors. I must make sure the pin list and the transistor connections use the specified ports correctly, to reflect a functional OTA and bias circuit. The transistor sizes have been chosen to meet or exceed these specifications while considering reasonable values for a 0.18um process.' config=ConfigFile(netlist='// Library name: MP3
// Cell name: ota
// View name: schematic
subckt ota VDD VSS ibp10u vin vip vout
    N1 (tail current VSS VSS) tsmc18dN w=10u l=0.18u m=1
